t the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io'], 'email-addr': ['psirt@paloaltonetworks.com'], 'url': ['https://docs.cyberark.com/find-identity-administration-docs/latest/en/content/getstarted/identity-new-doc-location.htm'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-45173']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-45172 - Idira Privileged Session Manager for SSH (PSMP): Arbitrary Command Execution via Improper Neutralization of Special Elements used in an OS Command', 'publication_date': 'Thu, 11 Jun 2026 22:16:57 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-45172', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['Due to incomplete input validation in Idira Privileged Session Manager for SSH (PSMP) versions prior to 15.0.2, 14.6.3, 14.2.5, and 14.0.6, an authenticated, low-privileged user could potentially execute arbitrary commands on the PSMP host. CyberArk Security Bulletins: CA26-17 and CA26-18', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-45172vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2026-45172weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io'], 'email-addr': ['psirt@paloaltonetworks.com'], 'url': ['https://docs.cyberark.com/pam-self-hosted/latest/en/content/release%20notes/rn-whatsnew14-0-6.htm', 'https://docs.cyberark.com/pam-self-hosted/latest/en/content/release%20notes/rn-whatsnew14-2-5.htm', 'https://docs.cyberark.com/pam-self-hosted/latest/en/content/release%20notes/rn-whatsnew14-6-psmp.htm#14.6.3', 'https://docs.cyberark.com/pam-self-hosted/latest/en/content/release%20notes/rn-whatsnew15-0-psmp.htm#15.0.2'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-45172']}}, {'title': 'Multiples vulnérabilités dans LibreNMS (11 juin 2026)', 'publication_date': 'Thu, 11 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000', 'source': 'https://www.cert.ssi.gouv.fr/avis/CERTFR-2026-AVI-0732/', 'source_type': "['operational', 'vulnerabilities']", 'source_level': 1, 'text': [], 'observables': {'url': ['https://github.com/librenms/librenms/security/advisories/GHSA-c9fv-cgmm-2wg7'], 'vulnerability': ['GHSA-C9FV-CGMM-2WG7']}}, {'title': 'Multiples vulnérabilités dans GitLab (11 juin 2026)', 'publication_date': 'Thu, 11 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000', 'source': 'https://www.cert.ssi.gouv.fr/avis/CERTFR-2026-AVI-0733/', 'source_type': "['operational', 'vulnerabilities']", 'source_level': 1, 'text': ["De multiples vulnérabilités ont été découvertes dans GitLab. Certaines d'entre elles permettent à un attaquant de provoquer une exécution de code arbitraire, un déni de service à distance et une falsification de requêtes côté serveur (SSRF)."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cve.org'], 'url': ['http://www.cve.org/CVERecord?id=CVE-2026-10087', 'http://www.cve.org/CVERecord?id=CVE-2026-10733', 'http://www.cve.org/CVERecord?id=CVE-2026-1500', 'http://www.cve.org/CVERecord?id=CVE-2026-3553', 'http://www.cve.org/CVERecord?id=CVE-2026-6269', 'http://www.cve.org/CVERecord?id=CVE-2026-6277', 'http://www.cve.org/CVERecord?id=CVE-2026-6552', 'http://www.cve.org/CVERecord?id=CVE-2026-6976', 'http://www.cve.org/CVERecord?id=CVE-2026-7250', 'http://www.cve.org/CVERecord?id=CVE-2026-8589', 'http://www.cve.org/CVERecord?id=CVE-2026-9204', 'http://www.cve.org/CVERecord?id=CVE-2026-9694', 'ht